  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5435",
  "title": "upgrading from Hogan templates to HTML tagged templates does not allow for custom attributes ",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nusing Hogan.js custom attributes were possible.  For example, adding custom click handler syntax to an anchor tag from 3rd party libraries like alpine.js   [https://alpinejs.dev/directives/on](url)\r\n```\r\n\r\n instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n     item (hit) { \r\n\r\n         return ' <a href=\"#\" @click.prevent=\"$dispatch('show-modal', { itemno: '${hit.itemno}' })\">'\r\n...\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow when upgrading to  HTML templates due to Hogan deprecation (https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/upgrade-guides/js/?client=html+tagged+templates#upgrade-templates),  the following error is thrown:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/380230/212973379-5e50de77-5633-425a-acef-c7aafae5b22d.png)\r\n\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nfollow the upgrade guide to replace them either with safe HTML strings using the provided html tagged template, or JSX templates as described above\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nsandbox.dynaprice.com\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nallow for custom attributes on dom elements.\n\n### Package version\n\n\"instantsearch.js\": \"^4.49.1\"\n\n### Operating system\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome v. 109.0.5414.74\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
